choices.text: Lea makes up new words by writing a nice looking string of characters on a piece of paper. She than erases a few of the most nasty looking characters and replaces them with underscores _ . After that she tries to replace the underscores with more acceptable characters trying to form a pleasant word. Lea considers words pleasant if they do not contain 3 sequential vowels, 3 sequential consonants and contain at least one letter L . In Croatian, the vowels are the letters A, E, I, O, and U only. All other lettters are consonants.
